<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Hundred Chart</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">This Hundred Chart enables children to visualize how numbers are arranged and organized. It can be used to teach about counting, skip counting, addition and subtraction.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Drag the green flip card on the left on any number. Use it to teach about one more, one less, ten more and ten less of that number. Click on the green cell to retrieve the hidden number.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Turn the Hundred Chart into a game to have fun with the children. The Hundred Chart Dice contains 6 faces which include +1, -1, +10, -10, +20 and -20. Drag a red chip to the centre of the Hundred Chart (e.g.: 45). Roll the dice by clicking on the roll button then move according to the dice. Let the children familiar with number pattern of the Hundred Chart. You may drag the red counter off the Hundred Chart to discard.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Use the paint features to demonstrate addition and subtraction. Select a colour then click on the number cell to paint it. Use the grey paint tool to remove the coloured cell. Click <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_hundredchart_cancel.png" style="vertical-align:middle"> to deselect the paint tool.</p>
</div>